---
// src/pages/about.astro
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="About AARBAA - Americans Against Road Bikers Association">
  <!-- Header Section -->
  <section class="text-center" style="
    padding-top: 100px !important;
    background-color: #0A3161;
    color: white;
    margin-top: 200px;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  ">
    <div class="container py-5">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
          <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-4">About Our Mission</h1>
          <p class="lead mb-0">From Satirical Beginnings to a Serious Cause</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Section -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10">
          <div class="card border-0 shadow-lg mb-5">
            <div class="card-body p-5">
              <h2 class="mb-4">Our Story</h2>
              
              <p class="mb-4">AARBAA began as a satirical response to the frustrations many Americans feel when sharing roads with cyclists who seem to forget that traffic laws apply to everyone. While our tone is humorous, our concerns are genuine.</p>
              
              <p class="mb-4">Founded in 2023 by a group of commuters who had experienced one too many close calls with cyclists ignoring traffic signals, AARBAA has grown into a nationwide community advocating for a simple but important cause: properly designated spaces for different types of road users.</p>
              
              <div class="row align-items-center my-5">
                <div class="col-md-5 mb-4 mb-md-0">
                  <img src="/images/protest.webp" alt="AARBAA Community Action" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" style="border: 3px solid #B31942;">
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-7">
                  <h3 class="mb-3">The Real Mission Behind the Satire</h3>
                  <p>While we poke fun at certain cyclist behaviors, our true mission is quite serious:</p>
                  <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li class="mb-2"><i class="fas fa-check-circle me-2" style="color: #B31942;"></i> Advocate for dedicated cycling infrastructure separate from main roadways</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><i class="fas fa-check-circle me-2" style="color: #B31942;"></i> Promote greater safety for <em>all</em> road users, including cyclists themselves</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><i class="fas fa-check-circle me-2" style="color: #B31942;"></i> Push for equal enforcement of traffic laws regardless of vehicle type</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle me-2" style="color: #B31942;"></i> Educate both drivers and cyclists about best practices for road sharing</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-light p-4 my-5 rounded" style="border-left: 5px solid #0A3161;">
                <h3 class="mb-3">We Are NOT Anti-Cycling</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">Many of our members are cyclists themselves. We don't oppose cycling as a form of transportation or recreation. Rather, we believe that proper infrastructure makes cycling safer and more enjoyable for everyone while reducing conflict on shared roadways.</p>
              </div>
              
              <h2 class="mb-4">Our Approach</h2>
              
              <p class="mb-4">AARBAA uses humor to highlight real issues, but our advocacy work is entirely serious. We work through these primary channels:</p>
              
              <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                        <div class="me-3" style="background-color: rgba(179, 25, 66, 0.1); width: 50px; height: 50px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
                          <i class="fas fa-bullhorn fa-2x" style="color: #B31942;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title mb-0">Awareness Campaigns</h4>
                      </div>
                      <p class="card-text">Using social media, local events, and eye-catching campaigns to draw attention to the need for separated infrastructure.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                        <div class="me-3" style="background-color: rgba(179, 25, 66, 0.1); width: 50px; height: 50px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
                          <i class="fas fa-gavel fa-2x" style="color: #B31942;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title mb-0">Policy Advocacy</h4>
                      </div>
                      <p class="card-text">Working with local governments to promote infrastructure solutions that benefit both drivers and cyclists.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                        <div class="me-3" style="background-color: rgba(179, 25, 66, 0.1); width: 50px; height: 50px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
                          <i class="fas fa-graduation-cap fa-2x" style="color: #B31942;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title mb-0">Education</h4>
                      </div>
                      <p class="card-text">Providing resources to help both cyclists and drivers understand their rights and responsibilities on shared roadways.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                        <div class="me-3" style="background-color: rgba(179, 25, 66, 0.1); width: 50px; height: 50px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
                          <i class="fas fa-users fa-2x" style="color: #B31942;"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title mb-0">Community Building</h4>
                      </div>
                      <p class="card-text">Creating a nationwide network of concerned citizens who advocate for better transportation solutions in their communities.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <h2 class="mb-4">Meet Our Team</h2>
              
              <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                  <div class="card border-0 shadow text-center h-100">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                      <div class="rounded-circle mx-auto mb-3 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; background-color: #0A3161; color: white;">
                        <span class="display-4">SJ</span>
                      </div>
                      <h4 class="card-title">Sarah Johnson</h4>
                      <p class="text-muted mb-3">Founder & Strategic Commander</p>
                      <p class="card-text">Former traffic engineer who became fed up with infrastructure planning that ignores reality.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-md-4">
                  <div class="card border-0 shadow text-center h-100">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                      <div class="rounded-circle mx-auto mb-3 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; background-color: #0A3161; color: white;">
                        <span class="display-4">MC</span>
                      </div>
                      <h4 class="card-title">Michael Chen</h4>
                      <p class="text-muted mb-3">Chief Education Officer</p>
                      <p class="card-text">An avid cyclist who believes that separated infrastructure is better for everyone on the road.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="col-md-4">
                  <div class="card border-0 shadow text-center h-100">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                      <div class="rounded-circle mx-auto mb-3 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; background-color: #0A3161; color: white;">
                        <span class="display-4">LM</span>
                      </div>
                      <h4 class="card-title">Lisa Martinez</h4>
                      <p class="text-muted mb-3">Legislative Liaison</p>
                      <p class="card-text">Former city planner with experience implementing successful separated bike paths.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="text-center mt-5">
                <h3 class="mb-4">Join Our Movement Today</h3>
                <a href="#join" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg px-5 py-3" style="font-family: 'Roboto Condensed', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px; font-size: 1.4rem;">BECOME A MEMBER</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section-padding" style="background-color: #0A3161; color: white; padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-8 text-center">
          <h2 class="mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <p class="lead mb-0">Answers to common questions about our organization and mission</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
          <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">
            <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
            <div class="accordion-item mb-3 border-0 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                  Are you really against cyclists?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="mb-0">No. Despite our tongue-in-cheek name, we're not against cycling or cyclists. We're against unsafe cycling behaviors and inadequate infrastructure that creates conflict between road users. We strongly advocate for dedicated cycling paths and protected bike lanes that create safer conditions for everyone.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
            <div class="accordion-item mb-3 border-0 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                  Aren't cyclists entitled to use the roads?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="mb-0">Yes, in most jurisdictions, cyclists have a legal right to use public roads. However, we believe that the safest and most efficient transportation systems provide separate infrastructure for different types of vehicles. Just as pedestrians have sidewalks separated from vehicle traffic, we advocate for cyclists to have their own dedicated pathways wherever possible.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
            <div class="accordion-item mb-3 border-0 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                  How do you respond to cyclists who say your organization promotes anti-cycling sentiment?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="mb-0">We understand why our satirical approach might be misinterpreted. However, our actual policy positions promote safer cycling through better infrastructure. Many of our members are cyclists themselves who recognize that mixing with motor vehicle traffic is dangerous and stressful. We believe that advocating for separated bike paths actually promotes cycling by making it safer and more accessible to people of all ages and abilities.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
            <div class="accordion-item mb-3 border-0 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
                  What specific policies does AARBAA support?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="mb-0">We support increased funding for protected bike lanes and separated cycling paths, better enforcement of traffic laws for all road users (including cyclists), improved education for both drivers and cyclists about sharing the road safely, and urban planning that prioritizes safe infrastructure for all transportation modes including cycling, driving, and walking.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
            <div class="accordion-item border-0 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
                  How can I get involved with AARBAA?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFive" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p class="mb-0">You can join our organization through the membership form on our website, follow us on social media to stay updated on our campaigns, attend local chapter meetings in your area (if available), or donate to support our advocacy efforts. We welcome anyone who shares our vision of safer roads with appropriate infrastructure for all users.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
